WorkItem.Description:
Create a new TypeScript file and input the following:

```
module TestModule {
    export enum MyType {
        Apples=1, Oranges=2
    }
    export class MyClass {
        public theType: MyType = MyType.Apples;
    }
}
```

If you right-click and refactor...rename MyType to something else such as MyType2, then MyClass.theType will be refactored, but the default assignment will remain MyType.Apples resulting in an error.
